  <para>
    <classname>MeshCenterFillDisplay</classname> fills each &mesh;
    element with a single color, determined by the value of a <link
    linkend="Section-Output-Scalar">scalar
    <classname>Output</classname></link> evaluated at the center of
    the element.  This is faster and cruder than a real contour map
    (<xref linkend="RegisteredClass-FilledContourDisplay"/> or <xref
    linkend="RegisteredClass-PlainContourDisplay"/>), which can
    display variations within an element.
  </para>
  <para>
    The <varname>what</varname> argument is the <link
    linkend="Section-Output-Scalar"><classname>Output</classname></link>
    to be plotted.
  </para>
  <para>
    The <varname>where</varname> argument determines where the output
    will appear. Elements may be drawn at their <link
    linkend="Output-Position-original">original</link>, undisplaced
    positions, at their <link
    linkend="Output-Position-actual">actual</link> displaced
    positions, or at <link
    linkend="Output-Position-enhanced">enhanced</link> positions.
  </para>
  <para>
    The <varname>colormap</varname> argument governs the translation
    from scalar values to colors.
  </para>
  

